tags.description: Mattie Brown Park is one of the most popular parks for children. It is located along the Little Butte Creek at the corner of Royal Avenue and Loto Street (129 South Royal). The 1.14-acre park is within walking distance of downtown.
tags.name: Mattie Brown Park

tags.description: Bob Moore Park is located off Main Street in downtown Eagle Point next to the Judge Stewart House. Bob Moore Park is the location of the city’s annual Christmas Tree lighting in December.
tags.name: Bob Moore Park

tags.description: Centennial Plaza is located in the heart of downtown at the corner of Main Street and Royal Avenue.
tags.name: Centennial Plaza
